In article <1s3r1r$48u@bigboote.WPI.EDU> wharmon@penny.WPI.EDU (Warren Harmon) writes:

>Yes, but sending encrypted information over the airwaves is illegal
>under some circumstances, does anyone know when exactly?

In the Amateur Radio Service, regulated by the FCC in the US of A,
prohibits encrypted transmissions, and other transmissions whose
purpose or intent is to obscure the content of the transmissions.
There are certain well specified exceptions, such as control links to
amateur radio satellites.

